# FinOps

- **Lean rules:** long procedures live in the **Local Brain** (`$BRAIN_PATH/resources/knowledge/operational/`), especially `claude-finops.md`.
- **Session:** brain-sync start/end and brain-load per sibling rules.
- **Habits:** `/clear` between unrelated tasks; in long work, also after a **theme or implementation-block switch** (`/rename` then `/clear` in Claude Code if resumable). **`/compact` early** in Claude Code with explicit keep-list (files, decisions, tests, errors). Optional shell: `CLAUDE_AUTOCOMPACT_PCT_OVERRIDE` — see `claude-finops.md`.
- **PRs:** `/create-pr` skill — gh + branch/commit conventions.
- **Bash hook:** RTK + tail cap on noisy install/build output.
- **Reference:** [FinOps Claude Code (sfeir.dev)](https://www.sfeir.dev/ia/finops-claude-code-comment-optimiser-sa-consommation-de-tokens/).
